    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-06-21T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-06-21T09:00:00-05:00" n="118"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d118">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">660F.116/171: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wright</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Praha</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-21T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 21, 1935—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 21—12:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>27. Your No. 17, June 18, 3 p.m., and instruction No. 49. Increased duty on all
                    lard imports, effective January 1st last as reported by Commercial Attaché in
                    his trade notes No. 464 of December 28, 1934,<note n="20" xml:id="d118fn20">Not
                        found in Department files.</note> more intensive competition from local
                    product and artificial substitutes, together with higher cost of American lard
                    make it practically impossible for the latter now to find a market in this
                    country irrespective of quota. Leading importer of American lard is selling off
                    his stock in hand at considerable loss and will make no further imports for the
                    present. Am pressing for equitable solution. Full details by mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wright</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
